<title>Set Facet Order</title>
<para>The order in which the facets are arranged in the program has to correspond to the order of the data file. The order is arranged according to the frequency, a given facet changes. The facets that change most slowly in the data file should be on top. The facet the changes most frequently should be on the bottom.</para>
<para>You can change the order of facets by mouse dragging and dropping appropriate facets up or down to achieve the desired order.</para>
<para>Each line in the data file is considered "a record" in analogy to the punched cards of yore. The corresponding facet needs to be "starred". You can add an asterisk (star) to the appropriate facet by simply clicking on it.</para>